# Python standards

- Python 3.11+; type-annotate all public APIs; mypy strict passes on `src/`
- Line length 100; Ruff format + lint (`make format`, `make lint`)
- Use `pathlib.Path` for filesystem paths; validate and resolve scan targets
- Never log or return full secret values — redact in normalized findings
- Engine adapters: `is_installed() -> bool`, `run(path) -> list[Finding]`, parse JSON/stdout defensively
- Subprocess: timeouts, capture stderr on failure, no shell=True
- Prefer stdlib + existing deps (`mcp`, `pyyaml`); avoid new deps without reason

```python
# ✅ subprocess with timeout
proc = subprocess.run(
    cmd,
    cwd=root,
    capture_output=True,
    text=True,
    timeout=timeout_s,
    check=False,
)

# ❌ never echo raw secrets
finding.code_snippet = redact_secret(raw_line)
```
